node.text: The new album is named for West’s late mother, who passed away in 2007. While DONDA explores a wider range of genres than his previous album Jesus is King, it features some of the religious themes that West has pivoted to in his recent music. A partial tracklist posted by West ahead of the release listed titles like “Pure Souls” and “Keep My Spirit Alive.” The album will be available for purchase and streaming on July 23rd.

node.text: Founded by Jeff Bezos, space travel company Blue Origin completed its first passenger flight on July 20. The rocket, named New Shepard, carried Bezos and three other passengers more than 65-miles above Earth, just to the boundary of space, known as the Kármán line. Watch our latest episode of HBNN to learn more.

node.title: @jeffbezos Completes His First Flight into Space

@hypebeastkicks: @newbalance’s retro-inspired 237 continues its busy year with a summer-ready makeover from @sizeofficial. The silhouette opts for a perforated base, while light grey suede overlays wrap around the uppers. Keeping a subtle look, the “N” logos are done up in a darker grey tone. An embroidered size? logo graces the insoles, while cream midsoles sitting atop a gray rubber outsole round out the release. The New Balance x size? 237 will drop exclusively on the UK-based retailer's webstore come August 6.⁠⁠

#hypeAF: @adidas has revealed its new 3D-Printed Eyewear. Weighing at just 20 grams, the matte black performance frames are built with the newest generation of 3D printers which weave a flexible nylon structure. A special coating creates a textured rubberized effect across the spiraling surface that houses the lightweight polycarbonate lenses. Limited to only 150 units, the sunglasses will be available on August 23 for $415 USD.⁠⁠
Photo: adidas

@hypebeaststyle: @manchesterunited and @adidasfootball have presented the club’s away jersey for the upcoming 2021/22 season. An optical art pattern has been engineered into the fabric, taking inspiration from the club’s snowflake design from the 1992 season, while “Solar Red” appears on the club crest, adidas’ three stripes, and sponsor logos. “Glory Blue” shorts nodding to the European Cup-winning side of 1968, and socks matching the jersey's blue/white optical pattern complete the kit that's now available from both the adidas and Manchester United websites.⁠⁠
Photo: adidas Football
